<tr><td>
<b>Penguin Computing</b> sells a series of Broadcom Trident based switches 
that run Cumulus Networks Software, a Linux adeptation.
The <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260106010546/https://people.ucsc.edu/~warner/Bufs/Penguin4804x.pdf">4804x</a> is based on the Trident+.  The
<b>x</b> variant has SFP+ slots while the <b>i</b> model [not pictured] 
has 48 tw-pr ports that limit top end speed to 1 Gb/s. 
We have seen a price quote and we are impressed. 
</td></tr>
</table>